        ],
        [
          "Clustering",
          "Higher Education",
          "B-Learning",
          "164 students",
          "1 Computer Science Course at Carnegie Melon University Spring 2019",
          "LMS logs, \nHomework and Exam Grades, \nStudent-level lecture and attendance logs",
          "None Specified",
          "[n-grams of sequences of activities with length 3, 4 or 5]",
          "Authors identify 37 types of clicks.^Clickstreams are divided into assessment weeks. \n\nAuthors create an embedding of the click types using a skip-gram model.\n\n\n\n",
          "Hierarchical Clustering,\nLatent Dirichlet Allocation",
          "Coherence score between sequences.",
          "9",
          "Group 1 - Looks at lecture notes\n\nGroup 2 - Look at Homeworks\n\nGroup 3 - Looks at recitation materials, \n\nGroup 4 - Catch up on news, \n\nGroup 5 Active HW Engagement, \n\nGroup 6 - Active Homework Engagement\n\nGroup 7 -Library Documentation\n\nGroup 8 - Tries Practice Exam\n\nGroup 9 - Look at practyice exam",
          "NLP-approaches can be used to analyze student’s learning strategies. \n\nActivity tends to increase before exams/homeworks, with students.",
          "Authors start by using pattern mining to extract sequences of activities. Similarity between patterns is computed using Jaro-Winkler distance.\n\nClusters generated are imbalanced. Smallest clusters have around 2 or 3 candiddate patterns.\n\nAuthors create a predicitve model that predicts assessment type based on the interactions of students → showing beihavior differs between homeworks and exams.\n\n\n\n",
          "Needs generalizability with more data/ techniques."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 5
    }
  ],
